    • Field Detail

      • STDF_CELL_WATER

        public static final javax.measure.Quantity<javax.measure.quantity.Dimensionless> STDF_CELL_WATER
        Solute transitional diffusion coefficient. Describes the ratio of D in cells to D in water. May be taken as a term to slow diffusion to account for the cytoplasmic density in cells.
        From: Kao, H. P., Abney, J. R., and Verkman, A. (1993). Determinants of the translational mobility of a small solute in cell cytoplasm. The Journal of cell biology, 120(1):175-184.
